__data__.text: Dear Residents,This is a mass email as a general reminder of housekeeping tips and tricks. Please read below to bestmaintain your apartment.A/CDue to Florida's heat, our office requires that you do not turn off your A/C at anytime. Instead, keep the fansetting on AUTO, and increase the temperature if you are cold or are leaving for a period of time. Garbage DisposalDO NOT put the following down your garbage disposal:Rice, pasta, oats, or breadBonesNuts and shellsPits and seedsEgg shellsPotato peelsCoﬀee groundsNon-food materials Grease, oil, and fatFlushing ItemsPlease ensure you are flushing only toilet paper. Do not flush feminine products, "flushable wipes," or anyother miscellaneous item, otherwise a backup may occur.Valet Trash Inform yourself and your guests- NO loose trash is permitted at anytime inside the valet trash can. ALL trashmust be bagged and tied. This includes grocery bags, water bottles, or take out containers. The stairwell is ashared space between you and your neighbors. In the event there is a trash violation, your entire stairwell willreceive a fine. We hope this helps you take care of your home going forward. If you have any questions, don't hesitate toreach out to the leasing office!Regards, Jessica Marchlewski  / www.offcampushousingusf.com813-443-0944Sr. Property Manager
